# 🧩 Explanation of the Diagram

## 1. Users Layer
This layer contains the three main actors:
- Resident
- Service Provider
- Admin

Each user interacts with a dedicated interface.

---

## 2. Frontend Layer
This is the presentation layer that users interact with directly.

### Resident App
Used to:
- Browse services
- Request services
- Make payments
- Track orders
- Leave reviews

### Service Provider App
Used to:
- Receive new requests
- Accept or reject orders
- Update order status
- Manage availability

### Admin Dashboard
Used to:
- Manage all platform operations
- Control categories and services
- Monitor system usage
- Resolve issues

---

## 3. Backend Layer
This is the core logic of the system.

### Authentication & Authorization Module
Responsible for:
- Signup / login
- Password protection
- Role-based access control

### User Management Module
Responsible for:
- User profiles
- Provider profiles
- Account data updates

### Service Management Module
Responsible for:
- Creating service categories
- Managing services
- Uploading service information

### Order Management Module
Responsible for:
- Creating service requests
- Assigning requests
- Tracking order status

### Payment Module
Responsible for:
- Processing online payments
- Verifying transactions
- Updating payment status

### Review & Rating Module
Responsible for:
- Saving user ratings
- Managing provider reviews
- Improving trust and quality

### Notification Module
Responsible for:
- Sending order alerts
- Sending updates to users and providers

### Location & Matching Module
Responsible for:
- Using map data
- Matching users with nearby providers
- Calculating distance and service coverage

### Admin Management Module
Responsible for:
- System control
- Reports
- Monitoring users, providers, orders, and complaints

---

## 4. Database Layer
Stores all main project data.

### Main Tables
- Users
- Providers
- Services
- Categories
- Orders
- Payments
- Reviews
- Locations
- Notifications

---

## 5. External Services Layer
These are third-party services integrated with the platform.

### Payment Gateway
Supports online payment transactions.

### Google Maps API
Supports:
- User location
- Provider location
- Distance calculations
- Nearby service discovery

### Firebase Cloud Messaging
Supports real-time notifications.

### Cloud Storage
Stores:
- User profile images
- Provider documents
- Service images

